item.title: Dell Medical School
item.description: The Dell Medical School is the graduate medical school of The University of Texas at Austin in Austin, Texas. The school opened to the inaugural class of 50 students in the summer of 2016 as the newest of 18 colleges and schools on the UT Austin campus. S. Claiborne “Clay” Johnston, M.D., Ph.D., was named as the medical school’s inaugural dean in January 2014. In accordance with the Medical District Master Plan released in 2013, the University’s portion of the medical district is being constructed in four phases.
